data.text:
Brentford 3 (Wood 27, Strevens 70, Cort 90+4) Milton Keynes Dons 3 (Wilbraham 11, 90+3, Easter 55 pen)

Attendance: 5,209

Andy Scott, the Brentford manager, maintained his players got what they deserved when Carl Cort, a substitute, denied MK Dons victory with a goal in stoppage time. Brentford trailed three times and Scott said: “It was justice.” Sam Wood and Ben Strevens also scored for Brentford, while Aaron Wilbraham, with two, and Jermaine Easter were on target for MK Dons, whose manager, Paul Ince, said: “We’re gutted. People haven’t done their jobs.”
